<br>
I started to go rogue, but thought about it - I always go rogue! Then thought some more - remembered someone complaining how everyone and their brother on SZ was a rogue.<br>
<br>
So I decided to try a class I never played before. Enter me, as a newt wizard.<br>
<br>
Does a wizard ever get scary? I drove a few goodies out of Blackburrow and back into Everfrost by nuking from the far side of the zone, but a tag team delegation came back and handed me my head on a platter. I think the only reason the ones who ran off left is because I wasn't somewhere they could see me to fight back (bolt spells let me attack from the far side of the pit)<br>
<br>
If the first few levels weren't so anal I'd just restart - instead, might try creating a rogue on my second account. Or maybe something else?<br>
<br>
I don't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> plan</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> on this being my main server now, but it's kind of exciting looking for places to hide and /con every time someone comes into view.<br>
<br>
While I'm here, any newt guilds looking for a newt newb wizard? Any suggestions on where a new lowb newt could go and have a chance of a decent fight?<br>
<br>
<br>
Sterlan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/5/01 2:28:42 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ouch, lol!</span><hr size=1> <br>
For low level PvP, just find an xp zone that's slightly below your own level range. If you're level 16, nail inkies in EC. If you're level 24, kill players in Oasis. That's at least how you do it when the attack range is limited, like on Vallon Zek.<br>
<br>
A wizard have it a bit tough below level 12 since root costs too much mana to cast. But at 12 you get a DD that has a knockback effect, which is useful. Also, expect to be owned hardcore by twinked melee players, and at lower levels, by pet casters. It does get better at higher levels even though you'll fall behind most classes in the high end game play.<br>
<br>
Surprise is a wizard's best friend in PvP. You'll want to have removed as much as half of the target's hps when he/she spots you and takes action. When I play my 53 wiz I want to find small groups or individuals peacefully medding after their last spiroc kill or whatever. That's when you whip out tears of druzzil quickly followed by draughts / lures / ICs. If you haven't killed your target within 20-30 sec, you might consider retreating and waiting for a better opportunity.<br>
